Problem: a car travels uphill at 30 km / hr and downhill at 70 km / hr . it goes 100 km uphill and 50 km downhill . find the average speed of the car ?
Rationale: avg speed = total distance / total time . total distance traveled = 100 + 50 = 150 km ; time taken for uphill journey = 100 / 30 = 10 / 3 ; time taken for down hill journey = 50 / 60 = 5 / 7 ; avg speed = 150 / ( 10 / 3 + 5 / 7 ) = 37 kmph answer : e
options: a ) 32 kmph , b ) 33 kmph , c ) 34 kmph , d ) 35 kmph , e ) 37 kmph
